definition: foot of a bird or animal/paw/claws/talons
(coll.) foot of an animal or bird/(coll.) foot supporting a cooking pot etc
surname Yin/abbr. for 印度[Yin4 du4]
to print/to mark/to engrave/a seal/a print/a stamp/a mark/a trace/image

sentences.english: On the ground I notice small, wet, paw prints.
sentences.chinese: 我发现地面上有小而湿的爪印。

sentences.english: She noticed the tracks of a fox in the mud.
sentences.chinese: 她看到了泥地上的狐狸爪印。

sentences.english: Caller3: They were much too large to be a big dog.
sentences.chinese: 这些爪印太大了，不可能是一只大狗的。

sentences.english: The hunter spotted paw marks of a rarely seen animal on the snow.
sentences.chinese: 猎人在雪地里发现了一种罕见的动物爪印。

sentences.english: They won’t be changing the antenna design, putting the “grip mark” was a mistake, though.
sentences.chinese: 他们不会改变天线设计，然而“夹爪印”则是个失误。

sentences.english: Paw print, or pugmark, tracing is another common technique for counting tigers.
sentences.chinese: 爪印和老虎的足迹同样是常用的计算老虎数量的方法。

sentences.english: As he looked at it, water had already filled the bottom of it.
sentences.chinese: 当他瞧着那爪印时，水已经铺满它的底部了。

definition: trace/impression (e.g. footprint)/abbr. of 印子錢|印子钱[yin4 zi5 qian2], usury
bloody mouth (from devouring freshly killed prey)
